Text.string: It's time to take back Eden-6, and we'll start with the town of Reliance. I hired a gunslinger named Clay to lend a hand. He's waitin' for you outside the town.
Slick bastard, that Clay. A smuggler. I don't quite trust him, but he worked for my father, and he just might be our best shot at driving them zealots back into the mud from whence they came.
Few bandits down there, Vault Hunter. Show me how you kill.
Yeah, sure—but because I want to, NOT because you asked.
Whatever, just do it already!
Asshole.
Ah. Vault Thief's still alive. Guess I should've Anointed a few more of the family. That's the REAL power.
Remind me why I kept you alive all these years?
Oh, c'mon, don't be like that! We're havin' fun! Heh, right? And she walked away.
Find anything, Vault Hunter?

You'll have to excuse Ty, she's, uh, not used to sharing the spotlight. Y'see, when we were growin' up, our parents never let her out of their sight. Tyreen would leech anything she could get her hands on! Heh-heh... Then our mom died—uh, that one's sorta on Tyreen, but... After that, our dad decided we could never leave his side. He never said it, but he saw Tyreen as a monster—and I was just a freak, heh, by the way. But we left him and came to Pandora. What that old turd didn't get is that these days, a freak with an ECHOstream can be a star.
Time to jump! Good luck, Vault Hunter.
It's been real, Vault Thief.
That was some damn fine shooting. Vive la résistance!
Boom, Anointed! Heh-heh!
Have this. Key to my personal weapons cache. Take it. Just, uh, don't ask where I was hidin' it.
I'll make my way back to Reliance. See you there, Vault Hunter.

Bet you're wondering how Aurelia Hammerlock got all mixed up with the Children of the Vault. Before the invasion, I found out she was spying on her brother. Aurelia gave the Calypsos all they needed to take Eden-6 by surprise. Aurelia claimed she knew where the Vault Key was, too. Only she didn't. Turns out there are some secrets money can't buy.
Spoke too soon! Don't let your barrels cool just yet.
Weapons shed should be just over here.

Gotta hotwire this bastard. While I do, you take care of the riff-raff, and free a few Jakobs loyalists. Wainwright said the COV captured a Jakobs master gunsmith named Dalton. Let me know if you find him.
For the resistance!
Freedom ain't free. Costs more than most things—that's what the brainiacs call “philosophy”.
For Jakobs!
Hope springs eternal! Read that on a love letter once. Guy I killed was a lucky man, I guess.
All right, head on back to the weapons shed. I'm almost in.
While I'm lookin' for Dalton, watch my ass. Which is to say, don't let me get shot in it. Language ain't as precise as a bullet, but it can be just as deadly in the wrong hands.
Damn. Hope you came to fight.
Rgh, this still ain't crackin'. Might require some “encouragement” from your gun.
Smart shootin'! Electricity's like a wild stallion. Can't piss on it while it's runnin'. You're just gonna have to trust me on that, Vault Hunter.
Got a lock on Dalton, but right now we've got to secure the town! Hope you came to fight, because they came to die!
Easy, easy. I'm no fighter.
Keep your distance, that bandit's got reach!
My dear business partners, are you sure your... “family” is up to the task? I don't want to use the words “blistering incompetence”...
Then don't.
Let's see how you do against my Eridium-tier brothers and sisters.
Whoo, the fires of the resistance are a-smoking! Now to turn it into a bonfire!
You do the honors, Vault Hunter.
And the town is ours! I gotta hand it to ya, Vault Hunter. You're one smooth operator!
I'm more of a people person.

So begins the Resistance. I gotta tell ya, I've been all around this galaxy. Seen darkness and savagery you wouldn't believe... but those Calypso Twins and their followers? They are something else. Someone's gotta stop 'em, and I'm thinkin' it just might be you. Be seeing ya, Vault Hunter.

So, ya met the newest member of our growing family! Aurelia, that bitch is ice cold! She tried to kill her own brother! Can you imagine? Hahaha, hah! Heh.||Anyway, we're getting closer to the Great Vault. Whoever opens it will be the most powerful being in the universe. You get that, don't you, superfan? Wanting to be the brightest star in the sky? With a galaxy of followers shouting your name? Well, it's not gonna happen! The Great Vault is mine! You couldn't handle that kind of power, but I... I was BORN for it.
Over here, Vault Hunter.
Moze. I kill people for loot. And fun. And justice and stuff.
Amara. The Tiger of Partali. My fists are the stuff of legends.
I am FL4K, and that is all you need to know about me.
Clay? Think we crossed paths once on Junpai-7, on a smuggling job.
Well, we ain't gettin' in the front gate. Might know another way. Follow me.
There's the weapons shed. Now, how do we get in?
To the saloon! Let's fill our cups with bandit blood!
Name's Clay. I suppose you and I are here to start a Jakobs resistance. Mind tellin' me who I'm working with?
It's raining bandits! Shoot blindly into the sky!
The gas station's swarming with zealots! Fill 'em with lead!
Bandits lurking by that feed store! Feed 'em some lead!
Motel's alive with bandits! Let's free up some rooms!
All right, all right. Wainwright says you're quite the gunslinger! Now, let's see about crackin' open this town.
This'll just take a second—I used to be a smuggler. Let's see if I still got it.
Nice work, Vault Hunter. You find that gunsmith Dalton?
No. Just some scrubs.
Didn't see him. Just some randos.
No master gunsmith. Merely regular civilians.
Nope. Just some loyalists and whatnot.
Damn. We gotta find Dalton. But let's get into this weapons shed first. One problem at a time.
Now in my experience, a resistance needs two things: hope, and guns. But mostly guns.
That's Dalton's personal cache, but we ain't gettin' in there without the master gunsmith himself. Lemme see if I can locate him.
(assorted bandit screams; “kill them!”)
All right, regroup and reload. More coming!

Vault Hunter! Just so you know, I've already hired some enterprising people to acquire the Key fragments. Cost a small fortune, which I will earn back by taking a nap. Because I accumulate wealth in my sleep? That's what rich people do.
(assorted bandit screams; “kill them all!”)
Kill the Vault Thieves!
For the Calypsos!
Here they come, Vault Hunter!
I got this. My time to shine! Firehawk!
(assorted bandit screams; “the Vault Thieves must die!”)
So, we're gonna liberate this town, crack open its weapons cache, and put Jakobs guns back in Jakobs hands.
Holy crap—right outta thin air? They can still bleed though! Let's show 'em how!
Nice fightin'! That's the last of 'em.
Don't let us down!
Brothers and sisters, KILL THE HERETICS, IN THE NAME OF THE CALYPSOS! THE GREAT VAULT BECKONS!
(assorted bandit screams; “die!”)
This way.
But we're not done yet. Looks like the COV kidnapped Dalton. He's being held in an island lockup called Fort Sunshine. I'll stay here and hold the town—you free Dalton.
Dalton worked for Wainwright's daddy, too. Montgomery Jakobs' personal gunsmith. Dalton makes the finest firearms on the planet—we can't have his guns ending up in COV hands. We're gettin' him out.
Can't go in the front door—it's locked up tight.
Can't get in that way, Clay.
It would appear my path is blocked this way.
No goin' in that way, Clay. Is there another way? Maybe by the bay? What do you say?
Guess we'll need to find another way in. Take a look around. There's an old lookout nearby that might offer a nice vantage.
Don't know what Wainwright told ya about me, but that don't matter now. We've got a town to free and bandits to kill.
What about this overhead crane thing?
What about that crane up there?
Perhaps the overhead crane would serve our needs.
What about that crane thingy up there, eh?

Good idea. That'll do nicely. Unfortunately, it'll be a bit of a bear to get to it. You'll have to go through the lumberyard, and that's COV central. I'll make sure the door's open by the time you get there.
Fight on through there and find a way up to those shipping cranes. There must be a loading dock up there somewhere.

If you woke up ready to enjoy a non-standard and incredibly dangerous conveyance, today's your lucky day, 'cause it's time to ride the rails. Hop on up on one of them things, and take it straight to Fort Sunshine.
Bet it's quite a view up there. Now, you may be on your way to a hellhole of a prison island, but that don't mean ya can't appreciate the little things, y'know?
Once you jump, you better be ready for a fight, 'cause the COV like givin' up their prisoners about as much as a grog likes givin' up a human shin-bone.
Watch out, Vault Hunter. It's one of those freaks!
Head's up, fam! Vault Thief's come for the gunsmith. Secure the island!
Back off, Vault Thief! You'll have to pry that gunsmith out of my cold dead hands!
Damn fine slaughter. Sometimes you gotta take lives to save lives. There's a harsh wisdom to that, but damn it if it ain't true. Now figure out how to get Dalton outta there.
Yup. Still got it. Ha! C'mon!
There he is! The gunsmith himself! See if he's all right.
Thank you, Vault Hunter! Those cultists were tryin' to force me to make guns for 'em. The last thing I wanted to do was arm those bastards. Jakobs guns belong in Jakobs hands.
Smooth operator. Glad to have Dalton back on our side. Swing by so I can thank you proper.
Nice work, Vault Hunter. Point you at a thing, and it gets done.
Don't forget to open Dalton's cache. You earned that.
Zealots on the hill! Kill 'em dead!
Bet that long arm would make a nice back scratcher. Just sayin'!
The resistance needs your help, Vault Hunter.
We've got a man locked up who shouldn't be.
Uh... hey, sis? The Vault Thief's trying to rescue that gunsmith you snatched. Do your thing! The, the teleporty thing.
